President Muhamamdu Buhari has commiserated with the people of Jigawa State over the death of Emier of Dutse, Dr. Muhammadu Nuhu Sanusi. Please enable JavaScript This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  Before his death, the Emir was the Chancellor of Sokoto State University. Expressing sadness on the passing of the Emir, Buhari in a statement by his media aide, Garba Shehu, yesterday said:  ‘‘He was instrumental to the progress Dutse had achieved in the last three decades under his watch. He was a grassroots person who was loved by all.” The President conveyed his condolences and that of the nation to the Dutse Emirate, the government and people of Jigawa State over the sad loss.